### Configure Multiple Browser and Device Projects in Playwright Test

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testproject.md

Demonstrates setting up a Playwright configuration with multiple test projects for different browsers and devices. The configuration includes shared options like timeout and ignoreHTTPSErrors, plus project-specific settings for Desktop Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and mobile devices (Pixel 5 and iPhone 12). This allows running the same tests across all configured environments.

```javascript
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  // Options shared for all projects.
  timeout: 30000,
  use: {
    ignoreHTTPSErrors: true,
  },

  // Options specific to each project.
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      use: devices['Desktop Chrome'],
    },
    {
      name: 'firefox',
      use: devices['Desktop Firefox'],
    },
    {
      name: 'webkit',
      use: devices['Desktop Safari'],
    },
    {
      name: 'Mobile Chrome',
      use: devices['Pixel 5'],
    },
    {
      name: 'Mobile Safari',
      use: devices['iPhone 12'],
    },
  ],
});
```

