### Configure Playwright Test Basic Options

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-use-options-js.md

This configuration snippet demonstrates how to set fundamental options for all Playwright tests. It includes defining a `baseURL` for simplified navigation and specifying a `storageState` file to pre-populate the browser context, which is useful for maintaining authentication across tests.

```js
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  use: {
    // Base URL to use in actions like `await page.goto('/')`.
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',

    // Populates context with given storage state.
    storageState: 'state.json',
  },
});
```

