### Configure baseURL in Playwright Config

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-webserver-js.md

Set up baseURL in the Playwright configuration file to enable relative URL navigation in tests. The configuration includes a local dev server that runs before tests start. When baseURL is set to http://localhost:3000 and you navigate to /login, Playwright automatically resolves it to http://localhost:3000/login.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  // Rest of your config...

  // Run your local dev server before starting the tests
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run start',
    url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
  },
  use: {
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',
  },
});
```

