### Browser Environment Variables Configuration

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/params.md

Specify environment variables that will be visible to the browser instance. Configuration varies by language with support for different value types.

```APIDOC
## BROWSER ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES OPTION

### Description
Set environment variables that will be visible to the browser. Defaults to `process.env`. Implementation varies by language.

### Option Name
`env`

### Type
Object (key-value pairs)

### Language-Specific Details

#### JavaScript
- **Value Type**: string | undefined
- **Example**: `{ "NODE_ENV": "production" }`

#### C# and Java
- **Value Type**: string
- **Example**: `{ "JAVA_HOME": "/usr/lib/jvm/java-11" }`

#### Python
- **Value Type**: string | float | boolean
- **Example**: `{ "DEBUG": "true", "TIMEOUT": "30.5" }`

### Configuration Example (JavaScript)
```json
{
  "env": {
    "NODE_ENV": "production",
    "API_URL": "https://api.example.com"
  }
}
```
```

