### Configure Playwright Emulation Options

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-use-options-js.md

This example illustrates how to set various emulation options within Playwright's `use` object for global test configuration. It covers emulating 'prefers-color-scheme', setting geolocation, locale, granting browser permissions, defining a timezone, and configuring the viewport size to simulate different devices or environments.

```js
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  use: {
    // Emulates `'prefers-colors-scheme'` media feature.
    colorScheme: 'dark',

    // Context geolocation.
    geolocation: { longitude: 12.492507, latitude: 41.889938 },

    // Emulates the user locale.
    locale: 'en-GB',

    // Grants specified permissions to the browser context.
    permissions: ['geolocation'],

    // Emulates the user timezone.
    timezoneId: 'Europe/Paris',

    // Viewport used for all pages in the context.
    viewport: { width: 1280, height: 720 },
  },
});
```

