### Browser Proxy Configuration

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/params.md

Configure HTTP and SOCKS proxy settings for all browser requests. Supports proxy authentication and domain bypass rules to control which domains route through the proxy.

```APIDOC
## BROWSER PROXY OPTION

### Description
Configures network proxy settings for all browser requests. Supports HTTP and SOCKS proxies with optional authentication and domain bypass configuration.

### Option Name
`proxy`

### Type
Object

### Properties
- **server** (string) - Required - Proxy URL for all requests. Supports HTTP (e.g., `http://myproxy.com:3128`) and SOCKS (e.g., `socks5://myproxy.com:3128`) protocols. Short form `myproxy.com:3128` is treated as HTTP proxy.
- **bypass** (string) - Optional - Comma-separated list of domains to bypass proxy, e.g., `".com, chromium.org, .domain.com"`.
- **username** (string) - Optional - Username for HTTP proxy authentication.
- **password** (string) - Optional - Password for HTTP proxy authentication.

### Configuration Example
```json
{
  "proxy": {
    "server": "http://myproxy.com:3128",
    "bypass": ".com, chromium.org, .domain.com",
    "username": "user",
    "password": "pass"
  }
}
```
```
